I’m amped you’ve decided to focus on mastering Electric-type Pokémon!
As I said, there’s quite a surge of them in the vicinity. I wonder how strong of a current they could all make together!
Just thinking about it makes the hairs on my arm stand up. Or maybe that’s just the static electricity in the air?
Let’s go see these Pokémon in action! Chaaaaarge!
You’re wired for this, %PLAYERNAME%! Now how about spending some quality time with your new friends?
Spark spends as much time as he can with his Pokémon. His instinct for bonding with Electric types is always spot on!
And remember—if you encounter mighty Pokémon out there, try using GO Safari Balls!
Welcome back, %PLAYERNAME%! I’m sure your Electric-type pals were ec-static to spend time with you.
Did you get a chance to battle with them? Electric-type Pokémon are quite strong against Flying and Water types.
But do you know what they’re weak against? Why don’t you spend some more time with them and think on it.
I can corroborate your findings when you come back!
Great job! You’re fully plugged in when it comes to Electric-type Pokémon! Have you thought about their weaknesses?
Here’s a hint: that Golem you caught will be very effective against an Electric type.
That’s grounds for celebration—you’ve got it! Electric-type Pokémon are weak against Ground types. You could say they zap the energy from our high-voltage friends.
Why don’t you roll out your Golem against some Electric types and see for yourself?
As a memento of your Electric mastery, take this medal! I couldn’t be more proud.
Keep that spark alive, and it will continue to take you far.
With so many new Electric-type Pokémon by your side, I’m sure you’ll keep each other amped up for years to come.
Now, I’ve got just a few things left I could use your help with. Let’s finish strong!
Hey, %PLAYERNAME%! Good to see you. How’s your training going?
I’ve been thinking. With all there is to learn, how does a person know when they’ve mastered something?
Just a little food for thought. Anyway, did you notice anything interesting out there?
I was struck by the high number of Electric- and Poison-type Pokémon buzzing and bubbling about.
In fact, speaking of measuring mastery—this is an excellent opportunity!
This is your chance to put your training to the test! Which path will you take to prove your prowess?
All right! You’ve picked your poison! Er, Poison type, that is.
They say you should avoid toxic people, but learning about Poison-type Pokémon is sure to be both fun AND useful!
A challenge you’re ready for, I have no doubt.
Why don’t you start by collecting data on the Poison-type Pokémon in the area.
Just look at all the Poison-type Pokémon you’ve caught. And what excellent snapshots!
I’m confident you could also master Pokémon photography. You should give it a shot!
Ahem. Now that you’ve caught some Poison-type Pokémon, it’s time to get to know them better.
Sharing some Berries is an effective way to build your friendship. Let me know how it goes!
Excellent work, %PLAYERNAME%! You and your Poison-type Pokémon look like great pals already.
Poison types are especially strong against Fairy- and Grass-type Pokémon, but do you know what their weakness is?
Here’s a hint: these Pokémon may “soil” a Poison-type Pokémon’s victory!
Heh. You work on that, and I’ll work on getting some new material. You’ve got this!
Venom...denim? No, that—ah! %PLAYERNAME%! I certainly wasn’t practicing my puns. Anyway, your Poison types are looking stronger than ever!
I wouldn’t want to face off against your team. That is, unless I knew what they were weak against. Any ideas?

Ah, %PLAYERNAME%—I’ve got news. The leaders of Team GO Rocket—Arlo, Cliff, and Sierra—have been spotted in the area.
We still don’t know what their plans are for the Dynamax phenomenon, but whatever they are, those three will be carrying them out!
Follow the leaders and find out what they’re up to—and stop them, if necessary!
I’ll be mapping out our next move—I think I’ll have something by the time you’ve dealt with the leaders. Good luck!
It looks like my suspicions were correct—this goes all the way to the top: Giovanni.
We’ve got to put a stop to his schemes, and I know you’re the perfect Trainer to do just that.
Go and show him what you’re made of!
Excellent work! Couldn’t have done better myself!
I’m too familiar with Team GO Rocket to believe we’ve heard the last of Giovanni, but you’ve definitely thrown a wrench into their plans.
I want to check in on nearby Dynamax Pokémon, so please take care of any Team GO Rocket Grunts still hanging around.
Great job, %PLAYERNAME%! The Dynamax Pokémon are safe now, thanks to your courage and skill.
We’ll need to keep a close eye on Team GO Rocket as we keep up our research on the Dynamax phenomenon, though.
Call it a professor’s intuition, but I’ve got a feeling a gigantic discovery is just around the corner.
%PLAYERNAME%, I have MASSIVE news to share!
We’ve come across even more enormous Pokémon—and what’s more, they appear to have changed appearance altogether!
There are still a bunch of questions to be answered, but thankfully I have an expert team—you!
I’m going to dive into some research, and while I do, I’ll need you to investigate in the field. With your help, we’ll get to the bottom of this supersized mystery!
I hope you’re ready for big updates, %PLAYERNAME%! Based on my research, I believe we might be witnessing what’s called the “Gigantamax” phenomenon.
Gigantamaxed Pokémon seem to not only have altered size and appearance, but they also gain the ability to use a new move. This move seems to be unique to a given species of Gigantamax Pokémon.
We have to gather more data from these Pokémon at Power Spots. It’s a tall order, but I know you’re up to it.
I’ll keep up the research at the lab while you’re out investigating!
While you were out, a fellow professor confirmed my hypothesis—we’re observing the Gigantamax phenomenon!
Can you imagine the incredible new Pokémon forms waiting to be discovered? The possibilities are as enormous as the Pokémon themselves! I’m getting chills!
Nothing beats knowing there’s so much more for us to learn, and I can’t imagine a better research partner than you!
Your tireless efforts and incredible discoveries these past weeks have advanced our understanding of the Gigantamax phenomenon.
You've more than earned a well-deserved break. Why don't you take some time to relax and recharge?
Perhaps a peaceful stroll or a quiet picnic in your favourite spot. And don't forget to bring along your Pokémon buddy!
Just when we think we've seen it all, the Pokémon world surprises us with something as incredible as Gigantamax.
Each discovery truly feels like we're writing a new chapter in the grand book of Pokémon research.
Thank you for all of your hard work. Until next time, %PLAYERNAME%!
%PLAYERNAME%, I’m glad you’re here. I’ve been bombarded with reports of Team GO Rocket sightings!
Those troublemakers are up to something. I’m sure of it.
Let me know what you find out, and I’ll keep you updated on my end. And stay safe out there!
Glad you’re back. I’ve been reviewing these Team GO Rocket reports, and I think I’ve pieced together something troubling.
The evidence suggests that they’re trying to take advantage of the Dynamax phenomenon.
Can you imagine the chaos if they could harness that kind of power? We can’t let that happen!
Please stop Team GO Rocket from getting anywhere near any Dynamax Pokémon!
